SELECT group_name, metric_name, value FROM test_groups JOIN test_results ON test_groups.group_id = test_results.group_id JOIN test_metrics ON test_results.metric_id = test_metrics.metric_id WHERE value > 50;
SELECT strategy_name, COUNT(*) AS total_groups FROM marketing_strategies LEFT JOIN test_groups ON marketing_strategies.strategy_id = test_groups.strategy_id GROUP BY strategy_name;

SELECT strategy_name, metric_name, AVG(value) AS average_value FROM marketing_strategies JOIN test_groups ON marketing_strategies.strategy_id = test_groups.strategy_id JOIN test_results ON test_groups.group_id = test_results.group_id JOIN test_metrics ON test_results.metric_id = test_metrics.metric_id GROUP BY strategy_name, metric_name ORDER BY average_value DESC;

SELECT t.group_name, tr.conversion_rate, tr.revenue_generated FROM test_groups t JOIN test_results tr ON t.id = tr.group_id WHERE tr.conversion_rate > 0.1 ORDER BY tr.revenue_generated DESC;
SELECT tl.log_text, tl.log_time, tg.group_name FROM test_logs tl JOIN test_groups tg ON tl.group_id = tg.id ORDER BY tl.log_time ASC;

SELECT ep.parameter_name, ep.parameter_value, ms.strategy_name FROM experiment_parameters ep JOIN marketing_strategies ms ON ep.strategy_id = ms.id WHERE ep.parameter_name LIKE '%budget%' ORDER BY ms.strategy_name ASC;
